===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈkəʊ.hɔː(ɹ)t/}}, {{SAMPA|/"k@U.h@U.hO:(r)t/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈkoʊ̯.hɔɹt/}}, {{SAMPA|/"koU.hOrt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[accomplice]]; an [[associate]] in [[crime]].
#: ''He was able to plea down his sentence by revealing the names of three of his '''cohorts''', as well as the source of the information.''
# A [[group]] of people [[support]]ing the same thing or person.
# {{statistics}} A [[demographic]] [[grouping]] of [[people]], especially those in a [[defined]] [[age]] group.
#: ''The 18-24 '''cohort''' shows a sharp increase in automobile fatalities over the proximate age groupings.''
# {{military|history}} Any [[division]] of a [[Roman]] [[legion]]; normally of about 500 [[men]].
#: ''Three '''cohorts''' of men were assigned to the region.''
# A colleague.

